headline: 3 Reasons HIG is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Since July 2020, the S&P 500 has delivered a total return of 93.1%. But one standout stock has more than doubled the market - over the past five years, Hartford has surged 195% to $122.86 per share. Its momentum hasn’t stopped as it’s also gained 9.7% in the last six months, beating the S&P by 5.6%.
